
Overview of noun torrent

The noun torrent has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (1) downpour, cloudburst, deluge, waterspout, torrent, pelter, soaker -- (a heavy rain)
2. (1) torrent, violent stream -- (a violently fast stream of water (or other liquid); "the houses were swept away in the torrent")
3. flood, inundation, deluge, torrent -- (an overwhelming number or amount; "a flood of requests"; "a torrent of abuse")
